Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place a few @Salad Potatoes{500%grams} at a time in between two #wooden spoon handles{} on a #board. Make slices widthways at 3mm intervals, making sure not to cut the whole way through. Repeat with the remaining potatoes.

Put the potatoes onto a large #baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{35-40%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.

Pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} onto a large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and set aside.

In a large #bowl, add the @British Chicken Breasts{2}, @Lemon & Herb Seasoning{1%sachet}, a drizzle of @oil{} and pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and cook until browned, ~{5%mins} each side.

Once browned, transfer the chicken to the #baking tray{} alongside the veg and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the veg is tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{10-12%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Peppercorn Sauce ==

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Add the @Cracked Black Pepper{1%sachet} and @Cider Vinegar{15%milliliter(s)}, then allow the vinegar to bubble away.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{50%milliliter(s)} and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%mins}.

Lower the heat, then mix in the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams} and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%mins}. Remove from the heat.

== Finishing ==

When the potatoes have 5 mins remaining, remove the baking tray from the oven and sprinkle over the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%grams}.

Return to the oven and bake until golden and the cheese has melted, ~{5%mins}.

Meanwhile, return the (now empty) chicken pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} (no need to clean). Once hot, add the @Mangetout{80%grams} to the pan and stir-fry until tender, ~{2-3%mins}.

When the chicken is cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, reheat the peppercorn sauce if needed, adding a splash of @?water{} if it's a little too thick.

Cut the chicken widthways into 2cm slices, then plate up with the hasselback potatoes, roasted broccoli and mangetout alongside.

Spoon the peppercorn sauce over the chicken to finish.

Enjoy!